Parliament, Tuesday, 2 July 2019 – The newly constituted Standing and Select Committees on Appropriations will tomorrow kick-start their programmes for the 6th Parliament by receiving a briefing from the National Treasury.
	
	The joint meeting will be briefed on the department’s fourth quarter expenditure report for the 2018/19 financial year, as well as the 2019 Appropriations Bill.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 3 July 2019
	Time: 10 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M46, Marks Building Meanwhile, the Portfolio Committee on Defence and Military Veterans will be briefed on the budgets and 2019/20 Annual Performance Plans of the Department of Defence, Department of Military Veterans, the Armaments Corporation of South Africa (Armscor) and the Castle Control Board. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 3 July 2019
	Time: 10 am 
	Venue: Committee Room, GH 41, Good Hope Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
